    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/ive-always-taken-it-be-kobol#comment-7394" class="active">You can have an Earth, but not the Earth</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Wed, 2009-02-18 01:53.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>You can write a story of a planet that was colonized.  It just isn&#8217;t our Earth.  All the life on Earth is closely related.   Follow the link above about Ark stories to see more details of why you can&#8217;t make this work.   Our history is deep, and interwoven with the history of our animals (who have their own deep and different but intertwined history) and even with the geology of our planet.   And I mean more than our written history, I mean the full story, including all our migrations and the migrations of animals which tied to water levels and continental drift.  It all fits together.   You can&#8217;t just plop humans down in a recent time and make it fit, people have tried.</p>
